Is this a useful thread? No, I just needed to vent this

We can't "cancel" Putin, we can't hack this war or make a educational thread on how to avoid it. 

No one, but a bunch of powerful white men in extra fancy suits, can do something about it

And I can't even imagine the feeling of being there, of having your loved ones there

It pains me all the way here on Brazil to know it's happening, I just wish everyone minimally involved in this to have a bit of peace in their hearts and hope this comes to an end asap

There are children scared of a bomb dropping to their heads while they hold guns

That is not something anyone should be willing to take part of

Web3 is a super diverse space, so I bet there's someone out there who thinks this is okay

I ask you not to comment here please, I don't want to know your perspective, I don't want to read how you think this is in anyway reasonable
I am sorry if I don't answer you properly today, I just can't have my head 100% in anything but the fact that we are living in a world where someone still thinks that's tolerable

It's not a disaster

It's not okay

It's simple and raw power > people logic
Do not act like you don't know it: the violent oppression of war is nothing but one more desperate face of unending profit savy capitalism
